label("$G$",g,S);
label("$H$",h,W);
draw(a--b--c--d--cycle);
draw(e--f--g--h--cycle);
[/asy] The final Answer is 68
 ### Proof
 Since $AE = 2$, $EB = 8$, but since $EFGH$ is a square, $EH = EF$, and $AH = EB$ by ASA congruence of right triangles $AHE$ and $BEF$.
